Year = {2025},
Month = {2025 OCT 30},
Abstract = {The evolution of machine learning and large language models (commonly
   referred to as ``artificial intelligence{''} {[}AI]) presents both
   opportunities and challenges for teaching and learning across K-12 and
   higher education contexts globally. Among the most pressing concerns is
   that these tools can undermine the integrity of student assessment and
   evaluation systems. This article investigates this timely issue by
   examining the intersections between AI, academic integrity, and
   assessment innovations through a cross-national research synthesis,
   resulting in a novel model for educators, policymakers, and researchers.
   The proposed model promotes assessment policies and practices that
   support high integrity, authentic learning, and innovative student
   assessment in an era of generative AI.},
